@node "load" "Load Configuration File"
LOAD FILE:

 You  will  notice  that  you  do  have the option of loading a pre-defined
configuration  file  (normally  TrapDoor.CFG)  into TrapConfig.  This is to
give  even the novice TrapDoor user the ability to slice, dice, mangle, and
otherwise destroy a working configuration file...if they are lucky.
@endnode

@node "save" "Save Configuration File"
SAVE/SAVE AS:

 Once you  have  completely  confused  yourself with the myrads of avalable
buttons, menus, and other assorted goodies contained within TrapConfig, you
can elect to save the whole mess in one of two ways.

 1.   SAVE:   This  will save your file as "Mail:TrapDoor.CFG" -UNLESS- you
specified  a  different  filename in the LOAD requestor, in which case that
filename will be used instead.

 2.   SAVE  AS:   You  will be prompted with a file requestor to select the
filename to save your configuration selctions.  The default filename is the
same as the SAVE option above.
@endnode

@node "modem" "Preset Modem Settings"
MODEM SETTINGS:

 PROVEN Modem control strings, for many popular modems, are hard-coded into
the  pulldown menu selections.  Once again, these have been PROVEN, through
experience,  to work with the modems appropriate to the selection.  Results
may  vary  if  you  attempt  to  use  ZYXEL control strings with a USR Dual
Standard,  so  don't  be  a  putz, and select the wrong modem type!  Please
report any strings that give you any problems.
@endnode

@node "palette" "Palette Adjustments"
PALETTE ADJUST:

 In  the  interest of Personal Creativity, The Authors have installed a set
of  gadgets  that  can  be used to set the Palette on your trapdoor screen.
This  allows  you  to  adjust the colors of TrapConfig, and thus, TrapDoor!
This  allows  the  more adventurous amongst us the ability to set it to the
most  disgusting,  horrifying,  and  useless  color  combinations possible.
Freedom of choice, no matter how senseless, is the touchstone of our work!

@endnode

@node "windows" "Adjusting Window Sizes"
WINDOW SIZING:

 TrapConfig  offers  the novice and expert user the easiest way possible to
adjust  your @{"LogWindow" link logwindow} and @{"StatWindow" link statwindow} sizes.  You will be given two windows
to  adjust  to  your heart's content.  When you have them just how you like
them,  simply  press  the close gadget on the LogWindow and TrapConfig will
remember  the  sizes  and positions of your windows.  What could be easier?
@endnode

